],&quot;tag_slug__in&quot;:[],&quot;tag_slug__and&quot;:[],&quot;post_parent__in&quot;:[],&quot;post_parent__not_in&quot;:[],&quot;author__in&quot;:[],&quot;author__not_in&quot;:[],&quot;ignore_sticky_posts&quot;:false,&quot;suppress_filters&quot;:false,&quot;cache_results&quot;:true,&quot;lazy_load_term_meta&quot;:false,&quot;post_type&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;nopaging&quot;:false,&quot;comments_per_page&quot;:&quot;50&quot;,&quot;no_found_rows&quot;:false},&quot;tax_query&quot;:{&quot;queries&quot;:[],&quot;relation&quot;:&quot;AND&quot;,&quot;queried_terms&quot;:[],&quot;primary_table&quot;:&quot;wp_posts&quot;,&quot;primary_id_column&quot;:&quot;ID&quot;},&quot;meta_query&quot;:{&quot;queries&quot;:[],&quot;relation&quot;:null,&quot;meta_table&quot;:null,&quot;meta_id_column&quot;:null,&quot;primary_table&quot;:null,&quot;primary_id_column&quot;:null},&quot;date_query&quot;:false,&quot;request&quot;:&quot;SELECT SQL_CALC_FOUND_ROWS  wp_posts.ID FROM wp_posts  WHERE 1=1  AND wp_posts.post_type = &#039;post&#039; AND ((wp_posts.post_status = &#039;publish&#039;))  ORDER BY wp_posts.post_date DESC LIMIT 0, 12&quot;,&quot;posts&quot;:[{&quot;ID&quot;:210,&quot;post_author&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2019-10-03 11:16:27&quot;,&quot;post_date_gmt&quot;:&quot;2019-10-03 11:16:27&quot;,&quot;post_content&quot;:&quot;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 17px;&quot;&gt;That comes as no surprise in u201cOthello,u201d sharply directed here by Nigel Shawn Williams on a modern set with overly literal projections of trickling blood and what look like lice. (u201cIu2019ll pour this pestilence into his ear,u201d Iago tells us in one of his chilling soliloquies.) As the Moorish general in the Venetian army who marries Desdemona, the white pearl of that societyu2019s aristocracy, Michael Blake establishes the psychosexual drama from the start. He wears his confidence like a cockscomb but is clearly more at a loss in love than he ever was in war.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Though race canu2019t help but be a theme in u201cOthello,u201d it is not the main one here; Iagou2019s hatred, and Othellou2019s susceptibility to it, seem to stem less from each manu2019s response to outsiderness than from their common fear of cuckoldry. (Iago imagines that Othello has slept with his wife, Emilia, here a soldier in Desdemonau2019s retinue, not just her maid.) In a superb performance, Gordon S. Miller (a ringer for Tony Hale of u201cVeepu201d) gives us Iago as a hypercompetent desk jockey who turns, after hours, into a vicious, fake-news-spreading incel.&lt;/p&gt;ttntttt&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_01-1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;blog_single_01-1&quot; /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_01-2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;blog_single_01-2&quot; /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_01-3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;blog_single_01-3&quot; /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;tttnttttttPreviousnttttttNextnttt&lt;h2&gt;Book During Shoulder&lt;/h2&gt;ttntt&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 17px;&quot;&gt;By the time Emilia points out that the failings women regularly stand accused of are merely reflections of menu2019s worse ones u2014 u201cThe ills we do, their ills instruct us sou201d u2014 itu2019s too late for Desdemona. She has made her bed and will die in it. I left u201cOthellou201d thinking, oddly enough, about Vice President Mike Pence and other politicians who observe the u201cBilly Graham rule,u201d not allowing themselves, even at work, to be alone with women who arenu2019t their wives.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;That idea came into relief, in both senses, in u201cLittle Shopu201d and u201cPrivate Lives,u201d the sour Nou00ebl Coward comedy of divorce and infidelity. But it became most obvious when the tragedy of u201cOthellou201d flipped into the comedy of u201cMerry Wives.u201d The absurd fear harbored by Mr. Ford that his wife is sleeping with Falstaff is matched only by Falstaffu2019s absurd fantasy that Mistress Ford and her bestie, Mistress Page, are gaga for him.&lt;/p&gt;ttntttttttttt&lt;img width=&quot;870&quot; height=&quot;520&quot; src=&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_02.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; srcset=&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_02.jpg 870w, http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_02-300x179.jpg 300w, http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_02-768x459.jpg 768w&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 870px) 100vw, 870px&quot; /&gt;tttttttttttnttMr. Cimolinou2019s charming production is set in a town like Stratford at the time of the festivalu2019s founding in the early 1950s. (The set resembles what you see while wandering the residential streets.) Itu2019s an apt connection, not just because of the storyu2019s inherent theatricality: The women devise and enact u201cscriptsu201d of comeuppance for the men.ttntt&lt;blockquote&gt;u201c There are no secrets to success. It is the result of preparation, hard work, and learning failure u201dn&lt;cite&gt;- Tina Retina&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;ttntt&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Though they are radiantly successful, we are always aware that the success depends on leveraging their limited powers. (One scene is trenchantly set among hair dryers in a beauty salon.) Especially in the haunting conclusion, a community prank that suggests the birth of theater itself, I thought about how acting was one of the first professions available to women.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&quot;,&quot;post_title&quot;:&quot;Big Data Tools, &amp; Frameworks&quot;,&quot;post_excerpt&quot;:&quot;We were Inpulse and these were the ideals that we strived to uphold. In the end, it was the talented people and the unmatched work they did that mattered the most...n Legwork lives on in the things we created, our memories, shared experiences and, so we donu2019t forget, here for good measure. It has truly been an amazing decadeu2013goodbye.&quot;,&quot;post_status&quot;:&quot;publish&quot;,&quot;comment_status&quot;:&quot;open&quot;,&quot;ping_status&quot;:&quot;open&quot;,&quot;post_password&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;post_name&quot;:&quot;big-data-tools-frameworks-2&quot;,&quot;to_ping&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;pinged&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;post_modified&quot;:&quot;2019-10-03 11:16:58&quot;,&quot;post_modified_gmt&quot;:&quot;2019-10-03 11:16:58&quot;,&quot;post_content_filtered&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;post_parent&quot;:0,&quot;guid&quot;:&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/?p=210&quot;,&quot;menu_order&quot;:0,&quot;post_type&quot;:&quot;post&quot;,&quot;post_mime_type&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;comment_count&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;filter&quot;:&quot;raw&quot;},{&quot;ID&quot;:194,&quot;post_author&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2019-10-03 10:34:15&quot;,&quot;post_date_gmt&quot;:&quot;2019-10-03 10:34:15&quot;,&quot;post_content&quot;:&quot;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 17px;&quot;&gt;That comes as no surprise in u201cOthello,u201d sharply directed here by Nigel Shawn Williams on a modern set with overly literal projections of trickling blood and what look like lice. (u201cIu2019ll pour this pestilence into his ear,u201d Iago tells us in one of his chilling soliloquies.) As the Moorish general in the Venetian army who marries Desdemona, the white pearl of that societyu2019s aristocracy, Michael Blake establishes the psychosexual drama from the start. He wears his confidence like a cockscomb but is clearly more at a loss in love than he ever was in war.&lt;/p&gt;nThough race canu2019t help but be a theme in u201cOthello,u201d it is not the main one here; Iagou2019s hatred, and Othellou2019s susceptibility to it, seem to stem less from each manu2019s response to outsiderness than from their common fear of cuckoldry. (Iago imagines that Othello has slept with his wife, Emilia, here a soldier in Desdemonau2019s retinue, not just her maid.) In a superb performance, Gordon S. Miller (a ringer for Tony Hale of u201cVeepu201d) gives us Iago as a hypercompetent desk jockey who turns, after hours, into a vicious, fake-news-spreading incel.n&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_01-1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;blog_single_01-1&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;n&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_01-2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;blog_single_01-2&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;n&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://localhost/xcaliburdigital/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/blog_single_01-3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;blog_single_01-3&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;nPreviousnNextn&lt;h2&gt;Book During Shoulder&lt;/h2&gt;n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 17px;&quot;&gt;By the time Emilia points out that the failings women regularly stand accused of are merely reflections of menu2019s worse ones u2014 u201cThe ills we do, their ills instruct us sou201d u2014 itu2019s too late for Desdemona. She has made her bed and will die in it. I left u201cOthellou201d thinking, oddly enough, about Vice President Mike Pence and other politicians who observe the u201cBilly Graham rule,u201d not allowing themselves, even at work, to be alone with women who arenu2019t their wives.&lt;/p&gt;nThat idea came into relief, in both senses, in u201cLittle Shopu201d and u201cPrivate Lives,u201d the sour Nou00ebl Coward comedy of divorce and infidelity. But it became most obvious when the tragedy of u201cOthellou201d flipped into the comedy of u201cMerry Wives.u201d The absurd fear harbored by Mr. Ford that his wife is sleeping with Falstaff is matched only by Falstaffu2019s absurd fantasy that Mistress Ford and her bestie, Mistress Page, are gaga for him.nn&lt;img width=&quot;870&quot; height=&quot;520&quot; 